description: Ten years after the Rapture, a beautiful occultist and her pet demon embark on a road trip to the last open gateway to heaven in hopes of befriending God and escaping hell on earth. A bare-knuckle, action-driven series peppered with social commentary and dark humor, Strange Girl is a story about the bewildering nature of religion, what would happen if the dark future predicted by many came true, and what a good person would endure for not having faith in advance of it. Featuring story and art by a handful of today''s hottest new talents including Rick Remender (Uncanny X-Force, Venom), Eric Nguyen (Halo, Sandman), Jerome Opena (Uncanny X-Force, Punisher) and Nick Stakal (Criminal Macabre)

description:
Transformers Generations 2011 is a Japanese-exclusive series of two volumes published by Million Publishing throughout 2011. The series primarily showcases Transformers from the Japanese version of Dark of the Moon toyline, as well as Transformers United and other Japanese exclusives. The books also have concept sketches, design sketches, comics and interviews with some of Takara's employees. It is a followup to Transformers Generations 2010.

The first volume reprints the first 4 chapters of Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen: Unite for the Universe along with the previously unpublished 5th chapter. The second volume has an original story by Simon Furman and Guido Guidi.
name: Transformers Generations 2011
